title: Grateful Dead Live at Hollywood Palladium on 1972-09-09
lineage: MAR > R; sony ecm 22p's > sony tc-770; taped by Bruce Harvie; transfer: tdk 1800-sd 7" reel @ 3.75 ips, dolby b: technics rs-1506 > teac an-180 > benchmark adc1 24/96 > tascam hd-p2, adobe audition cs6 > cd wave > flac; transfer & seeded by Rob Berger
description:
Set 1

Promised Land, Sugaree, Me & My Uncle, Bird Song, Black Throated Wind, Tennessee Jed, Mexicali Blues, Deal, Playin' In The Band, Loser, Johnny B. Goode

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Friend Of The Devil, Jack Straw, He's Gone-> Truckin'-> The Other One, Stella Blue, El Paso, Casey Jones, Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: turn it up and you are there Beautiful sound on this.  THANK YOU

running out of adjectives this show sounds very similar to 1969-05-03 (in terms of sonics) ... but has the energy of a September 1972 show. It's perfect! If you ask me, this would do well on a desert island ... * Nick 12/22/2022
